ENTRY       EC 3.6.3.23                 Enzyme
NAME        oligopeptide-transporting ATPase;
            oligopeptide permease
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on acid anhydrides;
            Acting on acid anhydrides to catalyse transmembrane movement of substances
SYSNAME     ATP phosphohydrolase (oligopeptide-importing)
REACTION    ATP + H2O + oligopeptideout = ADP + phosphate + oligopeptidein [RN:R00086]
ALL_REAC    R00086
SUBSTRATE   ATP [CPD:C00002];
            H2O [CPD:C00001];
            oligopeptide [CPD:C00098]
PRODUCT     ADP [CPD:C00008];
            phosphate [CPD:C00009];
            oligopeptide [CPD:C00098]
COMMENT     ABC-type (ATP-binding cassette-type) ATPase, characterized by the presence of two similar ATP-binding domains. Does not undergo phosphorylation during the transport process. A bacterial enzyme that imports di- and oligopeptides.
